EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to health insurance coverage for surviving family members of deceased uniformed correctional and sanitation employees.
EventItemMatterName: Health insurance coverage for surviving family members of deceased uniformed correctional and sanitation employees.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Parks and Recreation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to renaming six thoroughfares and public places, Hillside Avenue, Borough of Queens, Douglas Road, Borough of Queens, Little Neck Road, Borough of Queens, Cherry Street, Borough of Queens, Willow Street, Borough of Queens, Boulevard, Borough of Queens and to amend the official map of the city of New York accordingly.
EventItemMatterName: Name Changes, Renaming six thoroughfares and public places

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to domestic partnerships.
EventItemMatterName: Domestic Partnerships

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright, A.638, “AN ACT authorizing the city of New York to reconvey its interest in certain real property acquired by in rem tax foreclosure in the borough of Manhattan to the person or persons who would have inherited said property from former owner Enola Walker, deceased, notwithstanding expiration of the two year period within which application may be made to the city to release its interest in property thus acquired; Block No. 1902, Lot No. 126 on the tax map for the borough of Manhattan”.
EventItemMatterName: In rem tax foreclosure, Enola Walker, Manhattan Block No.  1902, Lot No. 126 (A.638).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright, A.693, “AN ACT to amend the vehicle and traffic law, in relation to stopping at exits of parking garages in cities with a population of one million or more”.
EventItemMatterName: Vehicle and traffic law, stopping at exits of parking garages (A.693).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright, A.639, “AN ACT authorizing the city of New York to reconvey its interest in certain real property acquired by in rem tax foreclosure in the borough of Manhattan to Debora Unger and Anthony Marcus, notwithstanding expiration of the two year period within which application may be made to the city to release its interest in property thus acquired; Block No. 2074, Lot No. 15 and Block No. 1949, Lot No. 5 on the tax map for the borough of Manhattan”.
EventItemMatterName: In rem tax foreclosure, Debora Unger and Anthony Marcus, Manhattan Block No. 2074, Lot No. 15 and Block No. 1949 Lot No. 5 (A.639).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright, A.625, “AN ACT to amend the parks, recreation and historic preservation law, in relation to vacating a trust”.
EventItemMatterName: Parks, recreation and historic preservation law, vacating a trust (A.625).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright, A.753, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the regulation of commercial bicyclists”.
EventItemMatterName: Regulation of commercial bicyclists (A.753).

EventItemActionText: This SLR was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on State and Federal Legislation
EventItemTitle: State Legislation Resolution requesting the New York State Legislature to pass a bill introduced by Assembly Member Wright, A.1052, “AN ACT to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to penalties for building code violations”.
EventItemMatterName: Penalties for building code violations (A.1052).

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon sponsors of New York Fashion Week to adopt a healthy models awareness education campaign and to ban models with a body mass index of lower than 18.5 from walking the Fashion Week runways.
EventItemMatterName: Sponsors of NY Fashion Week to adopt a healthy models awareness education campaign and to ban models with a body mass index of lower than 18.5 from walking the Fashion Week runways.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the Council of the City of New York to declare a symbolic moratorium on the use of the “N” word in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Declare a symbolic moratorium on the use of the “N” word in NYC during the month of February, also known as Black History Month.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the contents of a lobbyist’s statement of registration, and to repeal subdivision (g) of section 3-213 of the administrative code of the city of New York, relating to the mailing of forms by the city clerk.
EventItemMatterName: Contents of a lobbyist’s statement of registration.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the designated geographic areas of commuter vans.
EventItemMatterName: Designated geographic areas of commuter vans.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Metropolitan Transportation Authority and the New York City Department of Education to provide additional rides on Student Metrocards or Supplemental Student Metrocards, and to extend the valid time limits of such cards in order to enable students to participate in school-related and after-school activities.
EventItemMatterName: MTA and the NYC Department of Education to provide additional rides on Student Metrocards or Supplemental Student Metrocards.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the preliminary mayor’s management report and the mayor’s management report to contain detailed information regarding the issuance of parking placards.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the preliminary MMR and the MMR to contain detailed information regarding the issuance of parking placards.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law in relation to the temporary task force to study the feasibility of transferring city-owned wetlands to the jurisdiction of the department of parks and recreation.
EventItemMatterName: Temporary task force to study the feasibility of transferring city-owned wetlands to the jurisdiction of the department of parks and recreation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the creation of a comprehensive wetlands protection strategy for New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Creation of a comprehensive wetlands protection policy for NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to workplace injury reporting requirements.
EventItemMatterName: Workplace injury reporting requirements.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to requiring the Director of the Mayor’s Office of Veterans’ Affairs to send annual written notice to all veterans within New York City informing them of federal, State and City benefits to which veterans and their families are entitled.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Director of the Mayor’s Office of Veterans’ Affairs to send annual written notice to all veterans within NYC informing them of federal, State and City benefits to which veterans and their families are entitled.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that the Mayor’s Office of Film, Theatre and Broadcasting notify and obtain input from the local Community Board and Council Member when restricting parking for more than 24 hours.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that the Mayor’s Office of Film, Theatre and Broadcasting notify and obtain input from the local Community Board and Council Member when restricting parking for more than 24 hours.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that all diesel fuel storage tanks located inside of buildings above the lowest floor and on rooftops and building setbacks be completely encased to provide added safety.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that all diesel fuel storage tanks located inside of buildings above the lowest floor and on rooftops and building setbacks be completely encased to provide added safety.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Civil Service and Labor
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Pension Boards of New York City and New York State’s various pensions to divest the City and State of any investments made in corporations doing business with Sudan until the genocide in Darfur ends.
EventItemMatterName: Pension Boards of NYC and NYS’s various pensions to divest the City and State of any investments made in corporations doing business with Sudan until the genocide in Darfur ends.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to providing notice to the state concerning disciplinary proceedings against certain professionals.
EventItemMatterName: Providing notice to the state concerning disciplinary proceedings against certain professionals.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the State Legislature to introduce and adopt, and the Governor to sign, legislation that would authorize the City of New York to adopt local laws to amend the Unincorporated Business Tax, the General Corporation Tax, and the Banking Corporation Tax to give tax credits to employers that hire qualified formerly incarcerated persons.
EventItemMatterName: NYC to adopt local laws to amend the Unincorporated Business Tax, the General Corporation Tax, and the Banking Corporation Tax to give tax credits to employers that hire qualified formerly incarcerated persons.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Consumer Affairs
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Public Service Commission to reject Con Edison’s Proposed M29 Transmission Line and Academy Substation Project and adopt the alternate route for the M29 Plan proposed by the Bronx, Manhattan, Yonkers M29 Joint Monitoring Committee.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Public Service Commission to reject Con Edison’s Proposed M29 Transmission Line and Academy Substation Project.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to eliminating the prearrangement and passenger manifest requirements for commuter vans.
EventItemMatterName: Eliminating the prearrangement and passenger manifest requirements for commuter vans.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that the commissioner of the department of transportation enforce the speed limits in the vessel regulation zone and the no wake zone by means of a photo violation-monitoring device.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that the commissioner of the DOT enforce the speed limits in the vessel regulation zone and the no wake zone by means of a photo violation-monitoring device.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring that all persons complete an approved boating safety training course before being permitted to operate small vessels in the waters around the City of New York.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring that all persons complete an approved boating safety training course before being permitted to operate small vessels in the waters around NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Government of Bangladesh to drop sedition charges against Salah Uddin Shoaib Choudhury.
EventItemMatterName: Government of Bangladesh to drop sedition charges against Salah Uddin Shoaib Choudhury.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Cultural Affairs, Libraries and International Intergroup Relations
EventItemTitle: Resolution recognizing and honoring Nancy Pelosi for her contributions to the advancement of women in politics and society at large, and on her election as the first woman in United States history to Speaker of the United States House of Representatives.
EventItemMatterName: Recognizing and honoring Nancy Pelosi for her contributions to the advancement of women in politics and society at large.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to including in the nuisance abatement law certain violations of the penal law and the alcoholic beverage control law.
EventItemMatterName: Including in the nuisance abatement law certain violations of the penal law and the alcoholic beverage control law.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the police department to submit reports concerning the discharge of firearms.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the police department to submit reports concerning the discharge of firearms to the council.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the City of New York, in relation to prohibiting the use of artificial trans fats by food service establishments and mobile food unit commissaries.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting the use of artificial trans fats by food service establishments and mobile food unit commissaries.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Fire and Criminal Justice Services
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to allowing New York City’s volunteer ambulance companies to purchase gasoline or diesel fuel, for their ambulances, directly from the New York City Fire Department or New York City Police Department.
EventItemMatterName: Allowing NYC’s volunteer ambulance companies to purchase gasoline or diesel fuel, for their ambulances, directly from the FDNY or NYPD.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to increasing penalties for construction-related violations.
EventItemMatterName: Increasing penalties for construction-related violations.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the process for a permit for a major alteration.
EventItemMatterName: Process for a permit for a major alteration.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to eliminating self-certification of plans submitted to the department of buildings regarding demolitions and certain alterations.
EventItemMatterName: Eliminating self-certification of plans submitted to the department of buildings regarding demolitions and certain alterations.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
